\title{swjm: Stagewise Variable Selection for Joint Models of Semi-Competing Risks}
\description{
Implements stagewise regression for penalized variable selection in joint
models of recurrent events and terminal events (semi-competing risks).

Two model frameworks are supported:
\itemize{
\item \strong{Joint Frailty Model (JFM)}: Cox-type model where
\code{alpha} = recurrence/readmission coefficients (first p elements of theta),
\code{beta} = terminal/death coefficients (second p elements).
\item \strong{Joint Scale-Change Model (JSCM)}: AFT-type model where
\code{alpha} = recurrence/readmission coefficients (first p elements of theta),
\code{beta} = terminal/death coefficients (second p elements).
}

Three penalty types are available:
\itemize{
\item \code{"coop"}: Cooperative lasso, which encourages shared support
between the recurrence and terminal event coefficient vectors.
\item \code{"lasso"}: Standard L1 penalty applied coordinate-wise.
\item \code{"group"}: Group lasso, which selects variables jointly across
both processes.
}
}
